---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import CallToAction from '../components/CallToAction.astro';
---

<Layout title="About | Front Yard Rebel" description="Learn about Front Yard Rebel and our mission to transform Jacksonville front yards with beautiful Florida native plants.">
	<!-- Hero Section -->
	<section class="py-20 bg-gradient-to-br from-moss-100 to-earth-100">
		<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center">
			<h1 class="text-5xl md:text-6xl font-bold text-moss-900 mb-6">
				About Front Yard Rebel
			</h1>
			<p class="text-xl text-moss-700">
				Transforming lawns, one native plant at a time
			</p>
		</div>
	</section>
	
	<!-- Story Section -->
	<section class="py-20 bg-white">
		<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
			<div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
				<!-- EDIT: Replace this placeholder content with your actual story -->
				<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-moss-900 mb-6">Our Story</h2>
				
				<p class="text-moss-600 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
					<strong class="text-moss-800">[PLACEHOLDER - Edit this section with your personal story]</strong>
				</p>
				
				<p class="text-moss-600 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
					Welcome to Front Yard Rebel! We started this journey in Jacksonville, Florida, with a simple 
					question: Why do we spend so much time, money, and water maintaining grass that doesn't 
					benefit our local ecosystem?
				</p>
				
				<p class="text-moss-600 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
					That question led us down a rabbit hole of research into Florida native plants, sustainable 
					landscaping, and the incredible wildlife that calls our state home. We discovered that by 
					replacing our traditional lawn with native plants, we could create a beautiful, low-maintenance 
					garden that actually gives back to the environment.
				</p>
				
				<p class="text-moss-600 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
					Now, we're documenting our entire front yard transformation on YouTube and Instagram, sharing 
					everything we learn along the way. From soil preparation to plant selection, from dealing with 
					HOAs to attracting pollinators – we cover it all!
				</p>
				
				<!-- Profile Image Placeholder -->
				<div class="my-12 text-center">
					<div class="inline-block w-48 h-48 bg-gradient-to-br from-moss-200 to-moss-300 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center">
						<div class="text-center">
							<span class="text-6xl">👤</span>
							<p class="text-moss-600 text-sm mt-2">[Your Photo]</p>
						</div>
					</div>
					<p class="mt-4 text-moss-500 italic">[Add your name and a brief bio here]</p>
				</div>
				
				<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-moss-900 mb-6 mt-12">Our Mission</h2>
				
				<p class="text-moss-600 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
					We believe that every front yard has the potential to be both beautiful AND beneficial 
					to Florida's ecosystem. Our mission is to:
				</p>
				
				<ul class="space-y-4 mb-8">
					<li class="flex items-start gap-3">
						<span class="text-moss-500 text-xl">🌱</span>
						<span class="text-moss-600">Inspire homeowners to embrace native plant landscaping</span>
					</li>
					<li class="flex items-start gap-3">
						<span class="text-moss-500 text-xl">📚</span>
						<span class="text-moss-600">Educate people about Florida native plants and their benefits</span>
					</li>
					<li class="flex items-start gap-3">
						<span class="text-moss-500 text-xl">🦋</span>
						<span class="text-moss-600">Create habitat for local wildlife, especially pollinators</span>
					</li>
					<li class="flex items-start gap-3">
						<span class="text-moss-500 text-xl">💧</span>
						<span class="text-moss-600">Promote water conservation and sustainable gardening practices</span>
					</li>
					<li class="flex items-start gap-3">
						<span class="text-moss-500 text-xl">🏘️</span>
						<span class="text-moss-600">Build a community of like-minded garden rebels</span>
					</li>
				</ul>
				
				<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-moss-900 mb-6 mt-12">Why "Rebel"?</h2>
				
				<p class="text-moss-600 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
					Let's face it – the traditional American lawn is the norm. HOAs expect it, neighbors 
					judge by it, and we've been conditioned to think it's the only option. Going native 
					means going against the grain. It means choosing ecology over conformity, sustainability 
					over convention.
				</p>
				
				<p class="text-moss-600 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
					Being a Front Yard Rebel means standing up for what's right for Florida's environment, 
					even when it's not the easy path. It means educating others, leading by example, and 
					showing that a native plant garden can be just as beautiful – if not more so – than a 
					traditional lawn.
				</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>
	
	<!-- Values Section -->
	<section class="py-20 bg-moss-50">
		<div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
			<h2 class="text-4xl font-bold text-moss-900 text-center mb-12">Our Values</h2>
			
			<div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
				<div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-2xl shadow-md text-center">
					<div class="text-5xl mb-4">🌿</div>
					<h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-moss-800 mb-3">Sustainability</h3>
					<p class="text-moss-600">
						Every decision we make considers the long-term impact on our environment and ecosystem.
					</p>
				</div>
				
				<div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-2xl shadow-md text-center">
					<div class="text-5xl mb-4">📖</div>
					<h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-moss-800 mb-3">Education</h3>
					<p class="text-moss-600">
						We share everything we learn, making native gardening accessible to everyone.
					</p>
				</div>
				
				<div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-2xl shadow-md text-center">
					<div class="text-5xl mb-4">🤝</div>
					<h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-moss-800 mb-3">Community</h3>
					<p class="text-moss-600">
						We're building a community of garden rebels who support and inspire each other.
					</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>
	
	<CallToAction 
		title="Join Our Community"
		description="Follow along on YouTube and Instagram to be part of the native plant movement in Jacksonville!"
	/>
</Layout>
